1
00:00:35,970 --> 00:00:38,770
=Angels and Guards=

2
00:00:38,770 --> 00:00:41,270
=Episode 6=

3
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:43,416
Why have you been so nice to me?

4
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:44,750
Because I like you.

5
00:00:56,166 --> 00:00:57,041
What did you say?

6
00:00:58,916 --> 00:01:00,083
Because I like you.

7
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:05,583
Don't joke about that, or I'll hit you.

8
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:07,250
Beat me to death and I'll still say it.

9
00:01:07,458 --> 00:01:08,458
I like you.

10
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:09,875
And I mean it.

11
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:15,875
No. You can't like me.

12
00:01:17,041 --> 00:01:17,833
Why not?

13
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:20,333
Because I swore an oath.

14
00:01:20,583 --> 00:01:22,250
I won't marry until I catch Leng Xin.

15
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,666
Then I'll help you catch him.

16
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:31,041
(Northern Bureau)
My lord, you personally promised me

17
00:01:31,416 --> 00:01:32,916
that if I defeated Commissioner Lu,

18
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:35,458
you would let me enter the Bureau's

19
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:36,666
chamber to read Leng Xin's file.

20
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:41,583
I said after

21
00:01:41,583 --> 00:01:43,750
you pass the month-end assessment
and defeat him.

22
00:01:46,250 --> 00:01:47,666
But I already defeated him.

23
00:01:48,083 --> 00:01:50,166
The assessment is only a formality.

24
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,125
Then finish the formality first.

25
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:56,791
Leng Xin's file is sitting right there.

26
00:01:56,791 --> 00:01:58,791
It won't grow legs and run away.

27
00:01:59,541 --> 00:02:00,750
Don't rush.

28
00:02:00,916 --> 00:02:02,125
A couple of days won't hurt.

29
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:03,166
Just a couple of days.

30
00:02:03,416 --> 00:02:04,041
Here.

31
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:05,708
Have a drink with me.

32
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:08,333
I heard

33
00:02:08,875 --> 00:02:11,750
you want to get into that chamber.

34
00:02:12,541 --> 00:02:13,291
You have a way in?

35
00:02:13,541 --> 00:02:14,541
To be honest,

36
00:02:14,625 --> 00:02:16,916
I've been

37
00:02:17,416 --> 00:02:18,708
quite interested in that chamber.

38
00:02:19,250 --> 00:02:21,375
And I've already asked Xu Duoyu

39
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,208
to get us a fake pass.

40
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,833
Xu Duoyu can forge passes?

41
00:02:26,208 --> 00:02:27,000
So?

42
00:02:27,083 --> 00:02:27,541
Are you coming?

43
00:02:28,583 --> 00:02:29,041
Wait.

44
00:02:29,791 --> 00:02:31,708
If you have a pass, why not go alone?

45
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:32,791
Why drag me into it?

46
00:02:34,208 --> 00:02:36,416
Because going alone

47
00:02:37,250 --> 00:02:38,666
is scary.

48
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:43,791
Commander.

49
00:02:43,875 --> 00:02:45,208
The matter you arranged is done.

50
00:02:48,470 --> 00:02:50,000
(Prince Luo's Treason Case)

51
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,333
(Why is there nothing in the chamber)

52
00:02:51,958 --> 00:02:54,208
(about why Leng Xin killed my father?)

53
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:57,875
(Who does he work for?)

54
00:03:05,890 --> 00:03:06,770
(Zhang Weimin)

55
00:03:07,125 --> 00:03:08,041
(What?)

56
00:03:09,083 --> 00:03:10,833
(When my father carried out
that mission,)

57
00:03:11,250 --> 00:03:12,500
(his direct superior at the time)

58
00:03:13,416 --> 00:03:14,791
(was Zhang Weimin?)

59
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,000
Greetings, Commissioner.

60
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:27,416
Here. Authorization.

61
00:03:29,916 --> 00:03:31,250
What are you two doing here?

62
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:33,375
Studying.

63
00:03:34,541 --> 00:03:36,166
Yes. It's quiet here.

64
00:03:40,208 --> 00:03:40,750
Good.

65
00:03:41,083 --> 00:03:41,708
Very good.

66
00:03:43,333 --> 00:03:44,375
That's the spirit.

67
00:03:55,375 --> 00:03:57,333
(If Zhang Weimin knows something,)

68
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,750
(how do I get it out of him?)

69
00:04:01,833 --> 00:04:03,750
(That old man may look muddled,)

70
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:05,375
(but he's actually very sharp.)

71
00:04:06,166 --> 00:04:07,083
(If he finds out)

72
00:04:07,083 --> 00:04:08,666
(I'm investigating a sealed case,)

73
00:04:10,041 --> 00:04:11,208
(will that cause trouble?)

74
00:04:12,416 --> 00:04:13,458
Three days from now

75
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:15,291
is the month-end assessment.

76
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:16,500
All of you,

77
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,958
don't think getting into the Bureau

78
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:19,291
means you can rest easy.

79
00:04:19,958 --> 00:04:22,125
Mr. Lu said that if even one

80
00:04:22,458 --> 00:04:23,750
of you three fails,

81
00:04:24,083 --> 00:04:25,250
all of you are out.

82
00:04:25,375 --> 00:04:26,291
Is that clear?

83
00:04:26,416 --> 00:04:27,041
Yes.

84
00:04:39,208 --> 00:04:39,791
What?

85
00:04:39,791 --> 00:04:41,791
Even you dare laugh at me?

86
00:04:50,208 --> 00:04:51,000
Nice shot.

87
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:52,375
Young Master Chang.

88
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:54,958
It's for you.

89
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:56,166
For me?

90
00:04:57,291 --> 00:04:58,125
Thank you, Young Master Chang.

91
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,416
To be Jinyiwei,

92
00:05:01,583 --> 00:05:03,125
you need more than martial arts.

93
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:05,750
You have real talent with a slingshot.

94
00:05:06,416 --> 00:05:07,291
I got good

95
00:05:07,291 --> 00:05:09,208
at shooting sparrows back in my village.

96
00:05:09,208 --> 00:05:10,625
Then make that your strength.

97
00:05:10,666 --> 00:05:13,000
If you make a good archer,

98
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:15,083
how could Zhang Weimin reject you?

99
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:17,041
Really?

100
00:05:18,041 --> 00:05:19,916
But you only have three days.

101
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:21,458
You need to train hard.

102
00:05:21,541 --> 00:05:22,833
You don't have to be perfect,

103
00:05:22,833 --> 00:05:23,916
but you can't miss.

104
00:05:24,166 --> 00:05:26,083
Otherwise, why would they keep you?

105
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:39,375
(The month-end assessment is tomorrow.)

106
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:41,625
(I have to pass.)

107
00:05:57,291 --> 00:05:59,458
Commander, Commissioner,

108
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:01,791
Shen Bingfan and Hua Mange

109
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,125
passed the month-end assessment.

110
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:07,583
Good.

111
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:09,583
Wait, wait.

112
00:06:09,625 --> 00:06:11,000
Isn't there still one left?

113
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,625
Yes, you. Come out.

114
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:18,833
Commander,

115
00:06:19,500 --> 00:06:20,916
I have something to report.

116
00:06:21,875 --> 00:06:22,333
What?

117
00:06:23,291 --> 00:06:23,958
Well...

118
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,625
I know

119
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,666
I'm not good with short weapons.

120
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:29,958
But I do have a special skill.

121
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,291
So I humbly ask

122
00:06:32,541 --> 00:06:35,291
if I may use this skill

123
00:06:35,666 --> 00:06:37,583
to make up for my short-weapons score.

124
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:38,541
Nonsense!

125
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:41,291
The assessment is not a game.

126
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:44,625
Let her speak.

127
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,666
What special skill does she have?

128
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:57,625
Everyone,

129
00:06:57,625 --> 00:07:00,666
this is just a village boy's toy.

130
00:07:00,708 --> 00:07:01,791
How is that a special skill?

131
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:03,833
What a joke.

132
00:07:18,375 --> 00:07:18,791
Good.

133
00:07:19,416 --> 00:07:21,208
Who here can't shoot down a bird?

134
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:22,208
Anyone can do that.

135
00:07:22,208 --> 00:07:22,875
Exactly.

136
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:23,958
Am I right?

137
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:25,708
Anyone can.

138
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:26,750
My lord.

139
00:07:27,125 --> 00:07:29,375
If the Southern Bureau hears about this,

140
00:07:29,375 --> 00:07:30,500
they'll laugh their heads off.

141
00:07:31,458 --> 00:07:32,291
Cheng Xintian.

142
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:34,083
Can that thing

143
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,500
only shoot birds?

144
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,291
I can hit pressure points from afar.

145
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,750
Stop bragging.

146
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:40,791
I'm not.

147
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:42,625
Strike a pressure point to prove it.

148
00:07:42,666 --> 00:07:43,500
All right.

149
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:46,250
Then let's do as Guokai said.

150
00:07:46,458 --> 00:07:48,791
We'll let her slingshot skills

151
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:50,458
count for the short-weapons test.

152
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:51,333
My lord.

153
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:53,166
That isn't what I meant.

154
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:54,625
I was saying this slingshot...

155
00:07:54,625 --> 00:07:57,041
Then what did you mean?

156
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:59,500
As the saying goes,

157
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:00,750
a man's word is his bond.

158
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,041
In front of all these people,

159
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:05,958
surely you won't go back on your word.

160
00:08:07,166 --> 00:08:08,041
Zuo Da. Jiang Biao.

161
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:11,666
And you there.

162
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:12,666
The second one.

163
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:13,958
Yes, you. Step forward.

164
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:40,250
Good shot!

165
00:08:40,375 --> 00:08:41,291
Didn't you say

166
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:41,625
you could

167
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:43,041
hit pressure points?

168
00:08:43,250 --> 00:08:43,833
Do it.

169
00:08:58,291 --> 00:09:00,000
Zuo Da, why are you laughing?

170
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,916
Sir, she hit my laughing point.

171
00:09:03,041 --> 00:09:05,041
Jiang Biao, why are you crying?

172
00:09:05,208 --> 00:09:06,333
She hit my crying point.

173
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:08,958
She hit my numbing point.

174
00:09:08,958 --> 00:09:10,958
I can't move.

175
00:09:10,958 --> 00:09:12,666
You two useless fools. Get out.

176
00:09:25,291 --> 00:09:26,250
You idiot.

177
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,083
Stand down.

178
00:09:35,125 --> 00:09:35,833
Stop laughing.

179
00:09:35,833 --> 00:09:36,541
All of you, stop!

180
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:40,583
Are you scolding me too?

181
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:41,416
I wouldn't dare.

182
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:44,500
In that case,

183
00:09:45,416 --> 00:09:46,291
Cheng Xintian,

184
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:49,625
although you failed the weapon test,

185
00:09:50,041 --> 00:09:53,500
your slingshot skill makes up for it.

186
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:54,333
I hereby decide

187
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:57,083
that all three female Jinyiwei
have passed.

188
00:09:57,458 --> 00:09:58,916
You may now take on missions.

189
00:09:59,916 --> 00:10:01,375
Wow!

190
00:10:08,166 --> 00:10:08,916
Guokai,

191
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,416
one must learn

192
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:12,416
to open up.

193
00:10:13,458 --> 00:10:14,291
Open up!

194
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,541
Open up!

195
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:24,458
Bingfan,

196
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:26,833
I passed!

197
00:10:37,916 --> 00:10:39,125
On such a wonderful day,

198
00:10:39,208 --> 00:10:40,458
let's drink again. Come on.

199
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:42,458
Cheers.

200
00:10:42,458 --> 00:10:43,958
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

201
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:48,958
Congratulations on passing, ladies.

202
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:50,666
My young master sends gifts.

203
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:54,000
How thoughtful of Young Master Chang.

204
00:10:54,958 --> 00:10:56,083
What are these?

205
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:58,125
Three Shu brocade cloaks.

206
00:10:58,375 --> 00:10:59,208
My young master said

207
00:10:59,458 --> 00:11:00,958
that when you travel for cases,

208
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:01,958
you may be exposed to the elements.

209
00:11:02,250 --> 00:11:04,666
These will shield you from the elements.

210
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,083
And three pairs of cloud-brocade boots.

211
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:07,666
Warm in winter and cool in summer.

212
00:11:07,666 --> 00:11:08,958
Also for you three female officers.

213
00:11:09,416 --> 00:11:11,875
How does he know all our shoe sizes?

214
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,875
You'll have to ask my young master.

215
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,750
He sent us gifts.

216
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:20,875
Let's not be difficult.

217
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:23,500
Honestly, Young Master Chang

218
00:11:23,583 --> 00:11:25,291
deserves much credit for this.

219
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:27,291
Now he's sent such fine gifts.

220
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:30,041
Shouldn't we go thank him?

221
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:33,810
(Emerald Pavilion)

222
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,666
Young Master, I came to thank you.

223
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:41,083
Without you,

224
00:11:41,291 --> 00:11:43,041
I wouldn't have passed the assessment.

225
00:11:43,708 --> 00:11:45,291
It was nothing. Don't mention it.

226
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:48,041
And you sent us gifts too.

227
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:49,416
Thank you.

228
00:11:49,833 --> 00:11:50,916
Only you came to thank me?

229
00:11:51,041 --> 00:11:51,791
They didn't?

230
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:54,000
I...

231
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:56,125
I'll thank you for them.

232
00:11:59,083 --> 00:11:59,583
Wait.

233
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:09,916
This red sandalwood slingshot

234
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:11,083
and these 24 steel pellets

235
00:12:11,208 --> 00:12:12,083
were mine as a child.

236
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:14,083
There's a pressure-point chart inside.

237
00:12:14,541 --> 00:12:16,083
I taught you three pressure-point shots.

238
00:12:16,333 --> 00:12:18,041
The rest is up to you.

239
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,125
Such a precious gift.

240
00:12:22,041 --> 00:12:22,833
Thank you.

241
00:12:23,250 --> 00:12:24,875
I'll study it carefully

242
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:26,625
and won't let everyone down.

243
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:28,375
Do your best.

244
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,500
What a strange dream.

245
00:13:43,458 --> 00:13:45,041
For once, it wasn't a nightmare.

246
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:47,333
Good thing it was only a dream.

247
00:13:52,310 --> 00:13:58,600
(Leisurely and Free)

248
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:01,250
Clear sky.

249
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,208
What lovely weather.

250
00:14:04,166 --> 00:14:06,583
Fresh and bright. Looking good.

251
00:14:07,890 --> 00:14:12,640
♪In a fleeting moment♪

252
00:14:14,180 --> 00:14:18,470
♪Whose face crosses my mind♪

253
00:14:20,350 --> 00:14:24,060
♪Whose name is it♪

254
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:25,375
No nightmare last night?

255
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:28,708
How do you know I have nightmares?

256
00:14:30,333 --> 00:14:32,708
Day one, you refused to share a room.

257
00:14:32,708 --> 00:14:33,750
That made me suspicious.

258
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,208
Most nights, you scream in your sleep.

259
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:38,750
Even through these thick walls,

260
00:14:38,916 --> 00:14:39,916
I can hear you.

261
00:14:40,916 --> 00:14:43,125
So... you heard everything?

262
00:14:43,625 --> 00:14:44,666
Do you have nightmares every night?

263
00:14:48,333 --> 00:14:49,541
Since I was thirteen,

264
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:51,916
I've had nightmares almost every night.

265
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:53,708
Have you sought treatment?

266
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:57,000
I've seen famous doctors.

267
00:14:57,416 --> 00:14:58,208
They said it was an emotional scar,

268
00:14:58,208 --> 00:14:59,041
with no cure.

269
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,125
Sit.

270
00:15:04,250 --> 00:15:05,208
I have a folk remedy.

271
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:05,916
Sit.

272
00:15:07,291 --> 00:15:08,083
Wait here.

273
00:15:10,560 --> 00:15:14,140
♪This longing cannot say♪

274
00:15:27,416 --> 00:15:28,583
Open it before bed,

275
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,458
and you'll never have nightmares again.

276
00:15:33,375 --> 00:15:34,833
If it can cure this old illness,

277
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:35,875
I'll be forever grateful.

278
00:15:52,680 --> 00:15:54,600
(A Night of Sweet Dreams)

279
00:15:55,125 --> 00:15:55,916
What?

280
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,666
(Place this portrait by your pillow.)

281
00:16:05,083 --> 00:16:06,875
(Pay your respects
before bed each night.)

282
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:08,833
(You'll sleep straight through
till morning,)

283
00:16:09,291 --> 00:16:11,291
(and all nightmares will vanish.)

284
00:17:57,333 --> 00:17:58,375
Did you sleep well last night?

285
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,708
I've never met anyone
so full of himself.

286
00:18:08,583 --> 00:18:09,291
Did it work?

287
00:18:11,166 --> 00:18:12,166
Did it?

288
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:36,770
♪Because you once entered my dreams♪

289
00:18:37,140 --> 00:18:40,520
♪Truth and illusion blur in wine♪

290
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:43,770
♪My heart drifted lost♪

291
00:18:43,770 --> 00:18:47,180
♪Yet found you in the crowd♪

292
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:51,480
♪My blood still burns
as the world surges♪

293
00:18:51,890 --> 00:18:55,230
♪The land is fair, and you are free♪

294
00:18:55,810 --> 00:18:58,020
♪Sword drawn, lost in obsession♪

295
00:18:58,020 --> 00:19:02,060
♪I've softly let it go♪

296
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:05,930
♪The vow you made was true♪

297
00:19:05,930 --> 00:19:09,680
♪Yet like clouds, it stops for no one♪

298
00:19:09,980 --> 00:19:11,890
♪Put away those dreamlike words♪

299
00:19:11,890 --> 00:19:16,430
♪And forget at world's end♪

300
00:19:16,730 --> 00:19:18,230
♪Embracing memory♪

301
00:19:18,230 --> 00:19:20,600
♪Through blossoms and dreams♪

302
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:24,480
♪You hide in the crowd, silent♪

303
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,810
♪I wish to let it pass♪

304
00:19:26,810 --> 00:19:31,810
♪And run toward this vast life♪

